                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="17759120" author="edimitrova" created="Fri, 25 Aug 2023 17:38:53 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I did not find any easy way to automate the detection of the base branch. Even if we rely on the C* version from build.xml, we still need to update for trunk when branching. If anyone has any quick ideas - I am open to hearing it. We can add a base_branch in build.xml, but it will still be one more thing to update on branching. The only plus will be that it can reside next to the cassandra_version for example so it will be harder to forget about it. We can probably make it one thing for all CIs when CI v2 is ready, and we have same scripts distributed in the different CI systems.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Patch: &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/ekaterinadimitrova2/cassandra/commit/4f212f5a791416d2bdd47c87eaa392af7bcfe3a2&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/ekaterinadimitrova2/cassandra/commit/4f212f5a791416d2bdd47c87eaa392af7bcfe3a2&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Tested locally like this:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
./generate.sh -p
Generating &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; config.yml file &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;for&lt;/span&gt; paid tier from config_template.yml
patching file ./config_template.yml
&#160;
Detecting &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; or modified tests with git diff --diff-filter=AMR cassandra-5.0...HEAD:
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=adelapena&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;adelapena&quot;&gt;adelapena&lt;/a&gt;&#160;, &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=mck&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;mck&quot;&gt;mck&lt;/a&gt;&#160;, do you mind taking a look when you have time? Thanks in advance&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17759124" author="adelapena" created="Fri, 25 Aug 2023 17:56:08 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I think the current patch is enough for now. Trying to read the base branch for&#160;&lt;tt&gt;build.xml&lt;/tt&gt; might work, but I&apos;m not sure it&apos;s worth it, since we have a new CI system coming that will probably be delivered before the next branching.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17759164" author="michaelsembwever" created="Fri, 25 Aug 2023 21:24:19 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Agree, the patch is good as-is, we just have to add it to the list of changes required in the &quot;Create release branch &#8230;&quot; tickets.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17759584" author="edimitrova" created="Mon, 28 Aug 2023 13:23:29 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thank you for the reviews, I will commit it soon&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17759586" author="edimitrova" created="Mon, 28 Aug 2023 13:35:16 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;To &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/cassandra.git&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/cassandra.git&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&#160; c611632eb5..e4c97f1925&#160; cassandra-5.0 -&amp;gt; cassandra-5.0&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&#160; 052a264741..269c04474f&#160; trunk -&amp;gt; trunk&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
